{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0664\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0664\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0664\"\nms.assetid: 60fe15a7-db22-414f-a7b8-fac79dad22b4\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0664\nLiteral of type double cannot be implicitly converted to type 'type'; use an 'suffix' suffix to create a literal of this type  \n  \n An assignment could not be completed; use a suffix to correct the instruction. The documentation for each type identifies the corresponding suffix for the type. For more information on conversions, see [Casting and Type Conversions](../../csharp/programming-guide/types/casting-and-type-conversions.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates CS0664:  \n  \n```csharp  \n// CS0664.cs  \nclass Example  \n{  \n    static void Main()  \n    {  \n        decimal d1 = 1.0;   // CS0664, because 1.0 is interpreted  \n                            // as a double.  \n  \n        // Try the following line instead.  \n        decimal d2 = 1.0M;  // The M tells the compiler that 1.0 is a  \n                            // decimal.  \n        Console.WriteLine(d2);  \n    }  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Type Conversion Tables](../../standard/base-types/conversion-tables.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0664\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0664\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0664\"\nms.assetid: 60fe15a7-db22-414f-a7b8-fac79dad22b4","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0664","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0664","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0664","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[172,193],"content":"Compiler Error CS0664","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0664","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0664","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Literal of type double cannot be implicitly converted to type 'type'; use an 'suffix' suffix to create a literal of this type","pos":[194,319]},{"content":"